{
  "texts": [
    "This paper is motivated by the interest in better understanding the public value that film festivals create for different beneficiaries.",
    "In this paper, we focus on the public value generation at the level of society, more specifically, the value of diversity created via film festival programming.",
    "We approach diversity as a multidimensional, multifaceted phenomenon.",
    "A festival's identity and orientation are defined through programming [8].",
    "Although the general understanding is that films seek out festivals, the festivals also need films to facilitate the construction of their identities [8, 50]."
  ]
}